**Key Auth Tests Expectations:**
- Registration: Creates user, returns JWT token (3 parts), no password in response, rejects duplicates/missing fields (201, 409, 400)
- Login: Returns token for valid creds (200), rejects invalid password (401), rejects non-existent users (401)
- Protected routes: POST/PUT/DELETE require auth token (Bearer token in Authorization header), GET is public
- Ownership: Only post owner can update (200) or delete own post; non-owner gets 403
- Comment protection: Similar pattern - creation requires auth, deletion restricted by ownership

