| Plaintext passwords | No `bcrypt` in deps; tests register then immediately login with same string |
| JWT payload: `{ userId, username }` | `userId` must be a number (test checks `typeof res.body.userId === "number"`) |
| `authenticate` as inline route middleware | Cleaner than global middleware; keeps GET routes public without extra logic |
| Module augmentation in `types.ts` | Cleanest location; file is already a module (has `export`) |
| `req.user!.userId` (non-null assertion) | Safe because `authenticate` always sets it before handlers run |

---

## Verification

Run `npm test` — all 3 test files should pass:
- `posts.test.ts`: GET endpoints still public; existing shape assertions unchanged
- `comments.test.ts`: GET endpoints still public; seed data intact
- `auth.test.ts`: All 5 describe blocks pass (Registration, Login, Protected Routes, Ownership, Comment Protection)

**Expected test state after auth.test.ts runs (shared in-memory db):**
- posts: 4 seed + 1 created by "authuser" = 5 total → `posts.test.ts` expects `≥4` ✓
- comments on post 1: 2 seed (auth test's comment is created then deleted) ✓

